{{Quote|Detecting a ''Sentinel''-class landing craft near planetfall. We're about to be raided by stormtroopers.|An Alderaanian, during Leia Organa's [[Mission to rescue the survivors of Alderaan|rescue mission]]|<ref name="Princess Leia 3">[[Princess Leia 3|''Princess Leia'' 3]]</ref>}}
A '''''Sentinel''-class landing craft''', also known as a '''''Sentinel''-class shuttle''', '''Sentinel assault shuttle''' or '''Imperial landing craft''', was a large-scale [[troop]] [[transport]] utilized by the [[Galactic Empire]]. During the early stages of the [[Galactic Civil War]], Imperials such as [[Agent]] [[Alexsandr Kallus]] and [[the Grand Inquisitor]] utilized these transports to either deploy [[stormtrooper]]s or to travel to a [[planet]]. Imperial [[Star Destroyer]]s carried these shuttles.

==Characteristics==
{{Quote|Would you look at that? An old Theta-class. Don't see many of those in service anymore.''"<br />"''I prefer the new Sentinel-class myself. More room to stretch out.|A pair of Lava Troopers|<ref name="Star Wars Adventures: Return to Vader's Castle 5">[[Star Wars Adventures: Return to Vader's Castle 5|''Star Wars Adventures: Return to Vader's Castle'' 5]]</ref>}}
[[File:Sentinel_class_shuttle-SWC.png|thumb|left|200px|A ''Sentinel''-class shuttle carrying a container]]
Designed by [[Sienar Fleet Systems]] in the shape of its cousin, the [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]], this larger, more spacious [[shuttle]] was primarily used to ferry a complement of 75 [[stormtrooper]]s into battle<ref name="Escape" />&mdash;55 more [[troop]]s than the ''Lambda''-class.<ref name="Ships of the Galaxy">''[[Star Wars: Ships of the Galaxy]]''</ref> The [[Starship|ship]] featured three wings: one stationary center foil and two articulated flanking wings.<ref name="Databank" /> The landing craft also had shielding strong enough to be able to withstand several hits from a [[Phoenix Nest|''Quasar Fire''-class cruiser-carrier's]] turrets.<ref name="Homecoming">{{Rebels|Homecoming}}</ref> They could also be modified with special containers carrying vehicles.<ref name="SWC">''[[Star Wars: Commander]]''</ref>

The shuttle also had two spotlights at the front of the craft.<ref name="Vision">{{Rebels|Vision of Hope}}</ref> It had several entry points, including a front ramp, a rear ramp,<ref name="Siege">''[[Star Wars Rebels: The Siege of Lothal]]''</ref> and doors to the side.<ref name="Chewbacca 4">[[Chewbacca (2015) 4|''Chewbacca'' (2015) 4]]</ref> The interior of the ship had a main passenger section and a cockpit. In the passenger/cargo area, there were benches and harnesses on each side with a ladder to the side of the front ramp leading directly to a hatch for cockpit access. The cockpit section had four seats.<ref name="Siege" /> The shuttle could also feature a refresher on the opposite side of the ladder.<ref name="DAD">{{Rebels|Double Agent Droid}}</ref>

==History==
====First deployment====
In [[18 BBY]], a ''Sentinel''-class shuttle transporting Major [[Lessa Banebreak]] and [[Squad 131]] of the [[Imperial Army]], which consisted of 10 [[TK stormtrooper]]s, landed on [[Tryth]]'s [[Fellian spaceport]] to try and help ISB Agent [[Sendril Crane]] apprehend [[Sohi]] and [[Clone Force 99]] <ref name="Sanctuary">''[[Sanctuary: A Bad Batch Novel]]''</ref>

====Later service====
{{Quote|Proceed to transport ID-83 for the naval academy at Carida. Good luck, Han Solo. We'll have you flying in no time. |Recruitment officer Drawd Munbrin|<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>}}
[[File:SentinelClassLandingCraft-SaS.png|thumb|left|200px|A ''Sentinel''-class landing craft landing on a rainy planet.]]
In [[13 BBY]], a young [[Han Solo]], desperate to escape the planet [[Corellia]], was recruited by the [[Imperial Military|Imperial armed forces]] stationed on the urban world. Seeking to become one of the galaxy's greatest [[pilot]]s, Solo initially applied for the [[Imperial Navy]], believing it to be his best chance at eventually acquiring a [[starship]] he could use to rescue his lover [[Qi'ra]], who had previously been captured by the [[White Worms]] gang. Having been given the surname "Solo" by [[Chief]] [[Imperial Recruitment Officer|Recruitment Officer]] [[Drawd Munbrin]], Han was told to report to transport [[ID-83]], a Sentinel-class lander, en route to the [[Carida Academy|Imperial Naval Academy]] on [[Carida]].<ref name="Solo" />

A ''Sentinel''-class shuttle was once used for [[transport]]ing the [[Imperial cadet]]s of the [[Academy for Young Imperials]] on the [[planet]] [[Lothal]] to a nighttime aquatic training mission.<ref name="Servants:Rebel">''[[Servants of the Empire: Rebel in the Ranks]]''</ref>

Stormtroopers and [[the Grand Inquisitor]] took a ''Sentinel''-class to [[Fort Anaxes]], an old [[Galactic Republic|Republic]] military base, to either capture or eliminate the [[Spectres]], after the rebels' successful mission to [[Rescue of Tseebo|rescue]] a former Imperial employee. After a brief battle on the abandoned base, the [[Jedi]] [[Kanan Jarrus]] piloted the ''[[Phantom]]'' and destroyed the shuttle before running away.<ref name="GF" />

[[Standard week|Weeks]] later, another one was used in the chase of the rebels and [[Senator]] [[Gall Trayvis]].<ref name="Vision" />

[[File:TarkinLothalArrival.png|thumb|left|200px|Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin arrives on Lothal in a ''Sentinel''-class shuttle]]
[[Minister]] [[Maketh Tua]] of Lothal was to take a shuttle on a meeting with [[Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin]] when she was rescued by the rebels, but after she boarded it, it exploded as part of a trap set by [[Agent]] [[Alexsandr Kallus|Kallus]] and [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]], killing her.<ref name="Siege" />

The rebels later became notorious for stealing shuttles, such as the shuttle [[Lagos (Sentinel-class)|''Lagos'']].<ref name="RR">{{Rebels|Rebel Resolve}}</ref> Later, a rogue former [[clone trooper]] [[Rex|CT-7567]], nicknamed Rex, and [[Jedi Knight]] Kanan Jarrus used another one of these stolen shuttles during their [[Rescue on the Imperial Interdictor|mission]] to destroy the [[Interdictor (Interdictor-class)|Imperial Interdictor]].<ref name="Stealth Strike" />

A ''Sentinel''-class shuttle was used by the Empire in an attempt to regain control of a Imperial carrier which was captured by the [[Spectres]] and members of the [[Free Ryloth Movement]]. Although the landing craft was destroyed when members of [[Free Ryloth Movement]] and the [[Spectres]] used the [[Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier|''Quasar Fire''-class cruiser-carrier]]'s [[laser cannon]]s to blast the landing craft.<ref name="Homecoming" />

Sometime during the [[Jedha insurgency]], the [[Guardians of the Whills]] [[Baze Malbus]] and [[Chirrut Îmwe]] joined with the [[Partisans]] to steal a shuttle. Although [[Saw Gerrera]] betrayed them and tried to take the shuttle to blow up the orbiting [[Star Destroyer]], the two Guardians were able to convince his troops to go through with the original plan&mdash;evacuating an orphanage.<ref name="Guardians of the Whills">[[Guardians of the Whills (novel)|''Guardians of the Whills'']]</ref>

Shortly before the [[Battle of Yavin]], at least one ''Sentinel''-class shuttle was deployed on [[Tatooine]] as the Empire searched for the [[droid]]s that were in possession of the stolen [[Death Star plans]]. On the planet, the shuttle flew over the [[Desert stormtrooper|sandtroopers]] of [[Foot Patrol 7]], who were sent to find the droids.<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

Shortly afterward, [[Commander]] [[Alecia Beck]] of the [[Imperial Security Bureau|ISB]] used one of the shuttles to carry a [[squad]] of stormtroopers off the ''[[Vehement]]'' during the hunt for [[Caluan Ematt]].<ref name="Smugglers">''[[Smuggler's Run: A Han Solo & Chewbacca Adventure]]''</ref>

